---
const poster = "/images/UntimelyHeroes13thHour.jpg";
---

<section
  id="untimely-heroes"
  class="snap-fold untimely-teaser"
  aria-labelledby="untimely-title"
>
  <div class="untimely-teaser__atmosphere" aria-hidden="true">
    <img src={poster} alt="" />
  </div>

  <div class="untimely-teaser__inner">
    <div class="untimely-teaser__poster">
      <img
        src={poster}
        alt="Untimely Heroes: The Thirteenth Hour"
      />
    </div>

    <article class="untimely-teaser__copy">
      <header class="untimely-teaser__header">
        <p class="eyebrow">RETURNING TO FALLENDRIFT</p>

        <h2 id="untimely-title">
          Untimely Heroes:
          <span>The Thirteenth Hour</span>
        </h2>
      </header>

      <div class="untimely-teaser__story">
        <p>
          Fallendrift is a city at the beginning of industrialization. Factories
          rise beside older neighborhoods and gas lamps burn over streets
          perpetually damp from rain. Coal smoke hangs over much of the city,
          trains come and go, and blacksmiths still repair wagon wheels and shoe
          horses.
        </p>

        <p>
          The wealthy live well, the poor do not, and most people know there are
          certain streets, buildings, and stories best left alone.
        </p>

        <p>
          But five years ago, something beneath Fallendrift was uncovered. Much
          of the city was destroyed. Many died and even more were driven insane
          by what they saw. And for a time, truth was impossible to ignore.
        </p>

        <p class="untimely-teaser__beat">
          But cities rebuild and forget.
        </p>

        <p>
          New buildings replaced old memories. Witnesses became drunks,
          eccentrics, liars, or those simply ignored. Horror turned first into
          local history, then rumor, then something parents mention only when
          children ask why no one lives on a certain street.
        </p>

        <p class="untimely-teaser__beat">
          Life went on.
        </p>

        <p class="untimely-teaser__final">
          Then on a particular clear, cool evening at thirteen minutes past
          midnight, every clock in Fallendrift struck once.
        </p>

        <p class="untimely-teaser__last-line">
          Even those without bells.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
